==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cloff
<hw>Cloff</hw> <pr>(kl⟦ocr⟧f; 115)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>Formerly an allowance of two pounds in every
three hundred weight after the tare and tret are subtracted; now used
only in a general sense, of small deductions from the original
weight.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>clough</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>McCulloch.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

